---
description: Timezone and datetime handling
alwaysApply: true
---

All datetimes in this codebase are UTC and timezone-aware.

- When parsing Open-Meteo responses, use `utc_offset_seconds` to convert local timestamps to UTC.
- SQLite stores datetime values as ISO 8601 strings with an explicit `+00:00` offset through
  `app.models.UTCDateTime`.
- Never use `datetime.utcnow()`. Always use `datetime.now(timezone.utc)`.
- Never introduce naive datetimes in application code.
- API responses serialize datetimes as ISO 8601 strings with explicit timezone information.
